					<p>From <a href="http://www.sovereignman.com/news-feed/uk-nanny-state-gets-milked-for-all-its-worth/">www.sovereignman.com</a></p>
<p>The UK nanny state is becoming even more apparent as loopholes are allowing citizens to get paid for doing almost nothing. The problem with social welfare is that inevitably people will exploit the system and leach money from the rest of the productive society. Here’s an eye-opening example of a UK women named Stephanie Fennessy-Sharp who is currently taking full advantage of her government’s handouts. According to <em>Business Insider</em>:</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration:underline;">“Sharp, 29, lives in Kent, England and has 10 children, but while she’s healthy and able, she and her 56-year-old husband Ian, a retired factory worker, choose not to work.</span></p>
<p><a href="http://www.sovereignman.com/news-feed/uk-nanny-state-gets-milked-for-all-its-worth/">Read more</a></p>
